The economically honest route is narrowing to two branches: `deposit()` is permissionless if the strategy already holds idle DAI, while `withdraw(uint)` can only be reached indirectly through the DAI vault/controller stack. IŌĆÖm writing the verifier to probe both in-path routes, use only real on-chain funding, and mark controller-only migration as infeasible unless the fork state itself exposes a public caller path.
Build a self-contained verifier that first probes the target's live fork-state, then executes only path-strict actions that remain permissionless from an external attacker.
